description: From Middle English arage, from Anglo-Norman arace, arache; apparently an irregular derivation from Old French arepe, from classical Latin atriplex, from Ancient Greek ἀτράφαξυς (atráphaxus), of unknown origin (probably a loan-word).

definitionGroups.group: The saltbush: any of several plants of the genus Atriplex

entries.meaning: or Atriplex patula, found in dry habitats, that have edible leaves resembling spinach.
(dated) Lamb's quarters: frost-blite (Chenopodium album) or another plant of the genus Chenopodium.
